label: TBM930_DIMMER_ON
author: Mobiflight Community
description:
This event is broken in SU5. To work around the issue modify the TBM930_Interior.xml file and add the following:

  <Component ID="MobiFlight_External_Control">
  	<UseTemplate Name="ASOBO_GT_Update">
  		<UPDATE_CODE>
        (L:MF_TBM930_LIGHTING_Dimmer_light_Set, number) d 0 > if{ 1 - (>B:LIGHTING_Dimmer_light_Set) 0 (>L:MF_TBM930_LIGHTING_Dimmer_light_Set) }
       		</UPDATE_CODE>
  		<FREQUENCY>1</FREQUENCY>
  	</UseTemplate>
  </Component>

Then use 2 (>L:MF_TBM930_LIGHTING_Dimmer_light_Set) to turn on the dimmer switch.

label: TBM930_IGNITION_ON
author: Mobiflight Community
description:
Sets the ignition switch to on

For post SU5 to get the switch to animate requires adding code to the TBM Interior XML file:
<!-- ############################################### -->
  <Component ID="MobiFlight_External_Control">
      <UseTemplate Name="ASOBO_GT_Update">
          <UPDATE_CODE>
         (L:MF_TBM930_ENGINE_Ignition_1_Set, Number) s0 0 > if{ l0 1 - (>B:ENGINE_Ignition_1_Set) 0 (>L:MF_TBM930_ENGINE_Ignition_1_Set) }
	             </UPDATE_CODE>
          <FREQUENCY>1</FREQUENCY>
      </UseTemplate>
  </Component>



_________

Once you have added the above code, set a custom event for ON PRESS/ON RELEASE:
For Auto:
1 (>L:MF_TBM930_ENGINE_Ignition_1_Set)

For On:
2 (>L:MF_TBM930_ENGINE_Ignition_1_Set)

For Off:
3 (>L:MF_TBM930_ENGINE_Ignition_1_Set)

  <Component ID="MobiFlight_External_Control">

            (L:MF_TBM930_FUEL_Selection_Set, Number) d 0 > if{ 1 - (>B:FUEL_Selection_set) 0 (>L:MF_TBM930_FUEL_Selection_Set) }
          </UPDATE_CODE>
          <FREQUENCY>1</FREQUENCY>
      </UseTemplate>
  </Component>

3 (>L:MF_TBM930_FUEL_Selection_Set)

to set fuel selection to auto.

author: Mobiflight Community
description:
(Learn how to apply this workaround: http://www.badcasserole.com/adding-workarounds-to-msfs2020-for-mobiflight/)

Turns the prop de-ice on, but due to a bug in SU5 the in-sim cockpit switch will not update. To work around the issue add the following to TBM930_interior.xml:

        <!-- ############################################### -->
  <Component ID="MobiFlight_External_Control">
      <UseTemplate Name="ASOBO_GT_Update">
          <UPDATE_CODE>
            (L:MF_TBM930_DEICE_Propeller_1_Set, Number) d 0 > if{ 1 - (>B:DEICE_Propeller_1_Set) 0 (>L:MF_TBM930_DEICE_Propeller_1_Set) }
          </UPDATE_CODE>
          <FREQUENCY>1</FREQUENCY>
      </UseTemplate>
  </Component>

Then do:

1 (>L:MF_TBM930_DEICE_Propeller_1_Set)

to turn off prop de-ice.

description:
(Learn how to apply this workaround: http://www.badcasserole.com/adding-workarounds-to-msfs2020-for-mobiflight/)

Turns the inertial separator on, but due to a bug in SU5 the in-sim cockpit switch will not update. To work around the issue add the following to TBM930_interior.xml:

        <!-- ############################################### -->
  <Component ID="MobiFlight_External_Control">
      <UseTemplate Name="ASOBO_GT_Update">
          <UPDATE_CODE>
            (L:MF_TBM930_DEICE_Engine_1_Set, Number) d 0 > if{ 1 - (>B:DEICE_Engine_1_Set) 0 (>L:MF_TBM930_DEICE_Engine_1_Set) }
          </UPDATE_CODE>
          <FREQUENCY>1</FREQUENCY>
      </UseTemplate>
  </Component>

Then do:

2 (>L:MF_TBM930_DEICE_Engine_1_Set)

to turn on the inertial separator.

label: TBM930_INERT_SEP_OFF
author: Mobiflight Community
description:
(Learn how to apply this workaround: http://www.badcasserole.com/adding-workarounds-to-msfs2020-for-mobiflight/)

Turns the inertial separator on, but due to a bug in SU5 the in-sim cockpit switch will not update. To work around the issue add the following to TBM930_interior.xml:

        <!-- ############################################### -->
  <Component ID="MobiFlight_External_Control">
      <UseTemplate Name="ASOBO_GT_Update">
          <UPDATE_CODE>
            (L:MF_TBM930_DEICE_Engine_1_Set, Number) d 0 > if{ 1 - (>B:DEICE_Engine_1_Set) }
          </UPDATE_CODE>
          <FREQUENCY>1</FREQUENCY>
      </UseTemplate>
  </Component>

Then do:

1 (>L:MF_TBM930_DEICE_Engine_1_Set)

to turn off the inertial separator. Note that if you apply this workaround then the in-sim switch is no longer usable if you trigger it via the Lvar.

label: Autobrake Low On
author: rofl-er
description:
Turns Autobrake LOW on
Note: this event is for On Press event.  Also requires the On Release event to properly activate the autobrake mode.
0 (>L:A32NX_OVHD_AUTOBRK_LOW_ON_IS_PRESSED, bool)
report_description: To properly set the autobrake mode, the event sets the Lvar to 1 on press, but does not provide the event to reset to 0 on release.  Should maybe change the name of the event to _PRESS and the companion to _RELEASE.

label: TBM930_BLEED_AIR_OFF
author: Guest
description:
This event only partially works in SU5: it will change the value internally but the switch in the sim will not update to display the current status.

To work around the issue modify the TBM930_Interior.xml file and add the following:

  <Component ID="MobiFlight_External_Control">
  	<UseTemplate Name="ASOBO_GT_Update">
  		<UPDATE_CODE>
            (L:MF_TBM930_PRESSURIZATION_Bleed_Air_Source_Set, Number) s0 0 > if{ l0 1 - (>B:PRESSURIZATION_Bleed_Air_Source_Set) 0 (>L:MF_TBM930_PRESSURIZATION_Bleed_Air_Source_Set) }
      </UPDATE_CODE>
  		<FREQUENCY>1</FREQUENCY>
  	</UseTemplate>
  </Component>

Then use  3 (>L:MF_TBM930_PRESSURIZATION_Bleed_Air_Source_Set)

label: WT_CJ4_GEN_L_RESET
author: Jaime Leon
description:
THIS EVENT REQUIRES MODIFICATION TO CJ4_Cockpit.xml
Lvar set here triggers event code in xml file with code below:
Code shown is for resetting of both Engine Generators
--------------------------------------------------
	<Component ID="MobiFlight_External_Control">
		<UseTemplate Name="ASOBO_GT_Update">
		<UPDATE_CODE>
		(L:MF_WTCJ4_Alternator_1_Reset,bool) if{ 
			2 (>B:ELECTRICAL_Alternator_1_Set)
			0 (>L:MF_WTCJ4_Alternator_1_Reset,bool) }
		(L:MF_WTCJ4_Alternator_2_Reset,bool) if{ 
			2 (>B:ELECTRICAL_Alternator_2_Set)
			0 (>L:MF_WTCJ4_Alternator_2_Reset,bool) }
		</UPDATE_CODE>
		<FREQUENCY>1</FREQUENCY>
		</UseTemplate>
	</Component>

label: WT_CJ4_GEN_R_RESET
author: Jaime Leon
description:
THIS EVENT REQUIRES MODIFICATION TO CJ4_Cockpit.xml
Lvar set here triggers event code in xml file with code below:
Code shown is for resetting of both Engine Generators
--------------------------------------------------
	<Component ID="MobiFlight_External_Control">
		<UseTemplate Name="ASOBO_GT_Update">
		<UPDATE_CODE>
		(L:MF_WTCJ4_Alternator_1_Reset,bool) if{ 
			2 (>B:ELECTRICAL_Alternator_1_Set)
			0 (>L:MF_WTCJ4_Alternator_1_Reset,bool) }
		(L:MF_WTCJ4_Alternator_2_Reset,bool) if{ 
			2 (>B:ELECTRICAL_Alternator_2_Set)
			0 (>L:MF_WTCJ4_Alternator_2_Reset,bool) }
		</UPDATE_CODE>
		<FREQUENCY>1</FREQUENCY>
		</UseTemplate>
	</Component>

label: ELEVATOR_TRIM_SET
author: Tuomas Kuosmanen
description:
Set elevator trim using a joystick axis. This assumes an axis that goes from 0 to 65535. If your range is different, you need to redo the math.

11/25/21 Note: event input range is actually -16383 to +16383. Confirmed the standard ELEV_TRIM_UP event only increases by 0.147% per click, so need to consider if this event is used for fine tuning

Note that this is for a short press of the button only.  For short or long press do the following:

Use MSFS Custom Event...

For On Press:
(E:SIMULATION TIME,second) 0.5 + (>L:myTshort)

& For On Release:
(E:SIMULATION TIME,second) (L:myTshort) < if{ (>H:AS3000_TSC_Horizontal_1_TopKnob_Push)  }

els{ (>H:AS3000_TSC_Horizontal_1_TopKnob_Push_Long) }

0 (>L:myTshort)


See more here for better understanding if desired ->https://github.com/MobiFlight/MobiFlight-Connector/wiki/MSFS2020-Short-and-Long-Press-Button-Configuration

label: TBM_CABIN_LIGHT_ON
author: Justin F
description:
This event requires adding code to the TBM Interior XML file:
<!-- ############################################### -->
  <Component ID="MobiFlight_External_Control">
      <UseTemplate Name="ASOBO_GT_Update">
          <UPDATE_CODE>
         (L:MF_TBM930_LIGHTING_Cabin_Light_Set, number) d 0 > if{ 1 - (>B:LIGHTING_Cabin_Light_Set) 0 (>L:MF_TBM930_LIGHTING_Cabin_Light_Set) }
	             </UPDATE_CODE>
          <FREQUENCY>1</FREQUENCY>
      </UseTemplate>
  </Component>



_________

Once you have added the above code, set a custom event for ON PRESS:
2 (>L:MF_TBM930_LIGHTING_Cabin_Light_Set)

AND for ON RELEASE:
1 (>L:MF_TBM930_LIGHTING_Cabin_Light_Set)

label: F16C_LEFT_ENG_FEED_INC

label: F16C_LEFT_ENG_FEED_DEC

label: F16C_LEFT_EXTLT_NAV_OFF

description: Extlt Nav Knob Dec.  Intended set encoder

label: F16C_LEFT_EXTLT_REFUEL_INC

author: Jaime Leon

label: F16C_LEFT_EXTLT_REFUEL_DEC

description: SPOILERS SET WITH POTENTIOMETER.  Assumes full range pot 0 to 1023.

code: (L:XMLVAR_Baro1_Mode) 2 > if{ 99 } els{ (L:XMLVAR_Baro_Selector_HPA_1,bool) if{ (A:KOHLSMAN SETTING HG, inHg) 100 * near } els{ (A:KOHLSMAN SETTING HG, mbar) near } }
label: A32NX_KOHLSMAN_SETTING
author: Jaime Leon
description:
Returns value for the Baro setting in inches Hg or millibars, depending on Baro Selector set to inches or millibars.
The value in inches Hg is multiplied times 100 to shift the value two decimal places so that Mobiflight can handle the two decimals in 29.92.
(L:XMLVAR_Baro_Selector_HPA_1), 0 = inches, 1 = millibars. 
In case Baro1 Mode is set to STD (value 2 or 3) this code will return a value of 99. This special value of 99 can be used in the Compare to set the display to show "STD".

label: ASCRJ_AP_TOGGLE
author: Jaime Leon
description: Toggle the autopilot by either engaging the AP ENG button or the AP DISC bar.  Intended for panels that do not have the AP disconnect button.

code: 7 (>A:BUS LOOKUP INDEX, Number)  1 (>A:CIRCUIT BREAKER PULLED:61, Bool) 100 *
label: KODIAK_BREAKER_STBYATT
author: Guest
